cons:
- Poor communication between departments;
- Salaries are not great, especially taking into account how tedious most positions in Sofia are. If the job's a compromise, the pay should be good!;
- Really bad tools... You'd think an IT company would invest in better automatisation and aid for its employees;
- Not sure if the CEO is to blame but company-wide the trend has been negative for a while now;
- Processes are not well thought out and really restrict creativity and one's ability to shine;
- While there are great people at the office, it feels like very few are motivated to do their job... many people are fed up with the bad decision making at management level;
- Constant change - but not for the better.
Advice to Management
Please start showing that you value your loyal, hard-working and high-achieving employees. Encouraging words every now and again are simply not enough, employees need financial incentives to keep their motivation high... Because, let's face it, the job portfolio for Bulgaria simply isn't interesting enough to offer other incentives. Focus more on understanding
