- Career progression was and continues to be limited due to all of the changes HP has been experiencing (the split to form HPE, merger with CSC and formation of DXC); 
- Workplace morale is very low due to the constant changes and the number of workforce reductions occurring; 
- Salary is dependent upon where you came from so no consistency
- Raises and recognition are virtually non-existent for the majority of employees; 
- As WFRs continue to occur, the workload of those let go is just pushed to those who remain and already over-burdened; 
- WFR's are part of every day life and expected as the company continually attempts to re-structure and reduce expenses to keep shareholders happy; 
- Allegiance is to the shareholders
Advice to Management
It is the people of a company who make the company, and in turn their customers, successful; HPE lost sight of the people many years ago and 'some' focus needs to return to the employee. Saying you care is not the same as showing. Employees will rally with you when they feel appreciated. I believe very few believe that to be true today. The people who remain don't feel safe, they are just waiting their turn, for the next wave of WFRs that they know are imminent. I wish the former CSC and HPE employees who remain, success as they embark as DXC but if the company culture does not change, it will be a lose-lose for everyone unfortunately
